This WWI Luger was manufactured as the standard issue sidearm to the German military. A very unique 100 year old specimen in good condition with a lot of history. The right side of the receiver displays all the Imperial Army acceptance stamps. Original grips are finely cut diamond shaped checkering made from walnut. The safety is marked "Gesichert" with the safe position being downward.  It comes with an original WWI 8 round magazine which has a numbered wood base.  The numbers on the upper portion (receiver) all match.  The lower portion (frame) also has matching numbers but they are different from the receiver.  The grips are number matching to the frame.

title: For Sale:  1847 Springfield Musket, Armi Sport.
postcontent:
1847 Springfield Musket, Armi Sport. This reproduction is true to the original measurements, with a 42" barrel and a total length of 58 inches. The Model 1847 was notable in several respects, chiefly that is was the last .69 caliber musket. Additionally, it was the first weapon made at both the Harpers Ferry and Springfield Armory with completely interchangeable parts. Harpers Ferry produced 103,000 while Springfield produced 172,000 for a total production surpassing a quarter of a million arms. Many of these arms had been delivered to militias in the late 1850s and saw service in the early years of the Great Conflict. This reproduction is nicely marked. The lockplate is stamped with Federal eagle in front of the hammer and vertically marked "Spring-field" in two lines behind the hammer. The lock and tang are dated 1847. The barrel is stamped with the correct style V.P. and eagle head proof marks are on the breech. The buttplate is marked U.S. The sling swivels are riveted as per the original. One piece American walnut oil finished stock. Weight 9.75 Lbs .Barrel length 42", 57 3/4" overall.
Smoothbore.

The rifle itself will come with a bayonet with scabbard as well. It has never been fired and is in good condition however it may need some re-polishing as it has been sitting in a room for some time.

I will only accept cash and I am looking for $550 for the rifle+bayonet&scabbard.
